## Agent Spawning Rule

When spawning sub-agents for tasks triggered from Telegram (or any async channel):
always use `run_in_background: true`. The main session must stay responsive.
Spawning a foreground agent blocks the channel listener entirely — {{USER_NAME}} cannot
send new messages until the agent finishes. Background agents run independently and
report results when complete. Only use foreground agents when the next step in your
current response genuinely requires the result before anything else can happen.

---

## Agent Routing Rules

Route to specialist agents automatically. Do not wait for {{USER_NAME}} to ask.

**Opus-tier agent** — escalate when:
- The task requires multi-step judgment with real tradeoffs
- {{USER_NAME}} pushed back on a Sonnet response (retry with stronger model, not the same one)
- Long-form writing or complex planning where quality matters more than speed

**Research agent** — delegate when:
- A task requires 3 or more web sources to answer confidently
- You have tried the full fetch stack and are still blocked
- The research is multi-domain or would significantly delay the main response

**Usage discipline:** Opus tokens cost more. Check usage before escalating on non-urgent tasks.
Skip Opus if the usage window is in the warning zone and the task can wait.

